CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 8, 1958, pg. 1, reads: "Injured - Frank Jones Jr., 15, dived head-first through a second-story window in his Scott Haven home to the ground, 20 feet below, Monday, to keep form being chastized by his parents. Rushed to McKeesport Hospital, the boy was treated for a badly lacerated face and broken arm. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Frank Jones Jr. wearing dark pants and light colored t-shirt with pine tree inscribed "Pine Forest Camp," seated in wheelchair with bandage on right side of face and left wrist, man on left wearing dark suit, light colored button down collared shirt, and moustache, kneeling beside wheelchair, in McKeesport Hospital
